---
import LessonLayout from '../../layouts/LessonLayout.astro';
---
<LessonLayout
  title="Robot Dance Party"
  track="little-explorers"
  week={7}
  phase="Phase 3: Creative Play"
  duration="30 min"
  emoji="💃"
  objective="Create a dance routine with Reachy"
>
  <section class="lesson-section mb-8">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-explorer-700 mb-3">🎯 Learning Objective</h2>
    <p class="bg-explorer-50 border-l-4 border-explorer-400 p-4 rounded-r-xl text-gray-700">
      Your child will combine sequences of movements to create a choreographed robot dance — applying everything from Phase 1 and 2.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="lesson-section mb-8">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800 mb-3">🛠️ Materials</h2>
    <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
      <li class="flex items-center gap-2">✅ Music player (any fun kids' song!)</li>
      <li class="flex items-center gap-2">✅ Computer + Python</li>
      <li class="flex items-center gap-2">✅ Paper to choreograph the dance steps</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="lesson-section mb-8">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800 mb-3">📋 Activity Steps</h2>
    <div class="space-y-4">
      <div class="flex gap-4 items-start">
        <span class="w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-explorer-500 text-white font-bold flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">1</span>
        <div><h3 class="font-bold">Choreograph Together (10 min)</h3><p class="text-gray-600">Design a 5-move dance on paper. Draw each move with arrows. Each move gets a name: "The Wave," "The Spin Head," "The Robot Shake."</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="flex gap-4 items-start">
        <span class="w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-explorer-500 text-white font-bold flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">2</span>
        <div><h3 class="font-bold">Code It! (10 min)</h3><p class="text-gray-600">Translate the dance to code. Run it. Does Reachy dance as planned?</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="flex gap-4 items-start">
        <span class="w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-explorer-500 text-white font-bold flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">3</span>
        <div><h3 class="font-bold">Dance Together! (10 min)</h3><p class="text-gray-600">Play the song. Run the code. Your child dances alongside Reachy doing the same moves. Record a video if you can!</p></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="lesson-section mb-8">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800 mb-3">💻 Code Snippet</h2>
    <pre is:raw class="bg-gray-900 text-green-300 rounded-xl p-5 overflow-x-auto text-sm leading-relaxed"><code># dance.py — Week 7: Little Explorers
import time

class ReachyMock:
    def move(self, description):
        print(f"🕺 Reachy: {description}")
        time.sleep(0.8)

try:
    from reachy_mini import ReachyMini
    robot = ReachyMini()
except Exception:
    robot = ReachyMock()
    print("🎮 Simulator mode — dance party!")

print("🎵 Starting Robot Dance Party!")
time.sleep(1)

# Your dance routine — add more moves!
dance_moves = [
    "The Wave — arm swings left to right",
    "The Spin Head — head turns slowly",
    "The Robot Shake — tiny arm vibration",
    "The Freeze — hold perfectly still",
    "The Bow — head tilts forward",
]

for move in dance_moves:
    robot.move(move)

print("🎉 Dance complete! Taking a bow...")</code></pre>
  </section>

  <section class="lesson-section mb-8">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800 mb-3">💬 Reflection Questions</h2>
    <div class="space-y-3">
      <div class="bg-yellow-50 border border-yellow-200 rounded-xl p-4"><p class="font-semibold text-yellow-800">🌟 "Which dance move was your favourite to design?"</p></div>
      <div class="bg-yellow-50 border border-yellow-200 rounded-xl p-4"><p class="font-semibold text-yellow-800">🌟 "Can you teach Reachy a NEW move we haven't done before?"</p></div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="lesson-section mb-8">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800 mb-3">👪 Parent Tips</h2>
    <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-xl p-5 text-gray-700">
      <p>💡 A list of moves in code is a list (array) — your child is programming data structures without knowing it!</p>
    </div>
  </section>
</LessonLayout>
